		"body": "## AI Assistance Disclosure\r\n\r\nUsed AI as a reference while navigating unfamiliar parts of the codebase. All code changes were written, reviewed, and tested by me.\r\n\r\n## What was happening\r\n\r\nWhen you created a table in the desktop RTE with a background colour (or any inline `style`) and then opened the same note on mobile and made any edit, the style was wiped on save.\r\n\r\nThere were two separate places stripping the attributes:\r\n\r\n1. **ProseMirror schema** (`packages/editor/ProseMirror/schema.ts`) — the `table` node override had no `getAttrs` in `parseDOM`, so `style`, `border` and `class` were silently discarded when the HTML was loaded into the editor. \r\n\r\n2. **Turndown GFM plugin** (`packages/turndown-plugin-gfm/src/tables.js`) — `tableShouldBeHtml()` only kept tables as HTML when they contained complex block elements (lists, headings, code, etc.).\r\n\r\n## What this PR changes\r\n\r\n- `schema.ts`: added `style`, `border` and `class` to the `table` node attrs, wired up `getAttrs` in `parseDOM` to capture them, and updated `toDOM` to re-emit them.\r\n\r\n- `tables.js`: added an early `return true` in `tableShouldBeHtml()` when the table node has a `style` attribute, so styled tables are always kept as HTML.\r\n\r\n- `schema.test.ts`: new regression test that creates an editor with a styled table and asserts the three attributes survive a parse → serialize round-trip.\r\n\r\nFIX:\r\nMarkdown: <div class=\"joplin-table-wrapper\"><table border=\"1\" class=\"jop-noMdConv\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; background-color: rgb(248, 202, 198);\"><tbody><tr><td><p>Test Task</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\r\n\r\nRTE: \r\n<img width=\"1356\" height=\"342\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0ccebf35-bac3-40bf-94af-da6b6504ced7\" />\r\n\r\nMarkdown: <div class=\"joplin-table-wrapper\"><table border=\"1\" class=\"jop-noMdConv\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; background-color: rgb(248, 202, 198);\"><tbody><tr><td><p>Test Task Soham</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\r\n\r\n",
